ing: 2 tablespoons olive oil, or as desired
2 cups finely crushed buttery round crackers (such as RitzÂ®)
salt and ground black pepper to taste
des: "This is my mom's recipe which is a favorite of my dad's and is quickly becoming a favorite at my house. The flavor of onions and zucchini blend nicely together in this recipe that will help use up the bountiful zucchini from your garden."
ins:
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Combine zucchini, crackers, onion, eggs, Cheddar cheese, salt, and pepper in a bowl using a spoon or your hands until mixture is evenly combined. Form mixture into small patties.
Fry patties in the hot oil until lightly browned and heated through, 2 to 3 minutes per side.
